      "content": "Mixing melatonin and zolpidem is not recommended, as it can lead to increased drowsiness and potential side effects. It's best to follow your doctor's instructions and use one medication at a time. If you're struggling with sleep, consider other non-pharmacological approaches such as maintaining a regular sleep schedule, reducing caffeine intake, and creating a comfortable sleep environment. Remember, your health is important, so always consult with your doctor before making any changes to your medication regimen.",
